<body>
    <h1>Task 22 - Setting Up a GitLab CE Server and Pushing a Flask Hello W=
orld Application code</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 local-id=3D"975b3c8e6a07" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServer=
andPushingaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-1.Introduction">1. Introduction</=
h3>
<h3 local-id=3D"14c1e08abcb0" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-1.1Purpose">1.1 Purpose</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d507564fc2e6">This Technical Document provides a detailed ac=
count of the implementation of a self-hosted GitLab Community Edition (CE) =
server on AWS EC2 and the deployment of a Flask Hello World application to =
a repository hosted on it. The intended audience for this document includes=
:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"39a28d3b5545"><strong>CTO</strong> =E2=80=94 for strategic o=
versight and validation of the self-hosted VCS approach</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a5a73e313e5d"><strong>Developers</strong> =E2=80=94 for unde=
rstanding the repository structure, Git workflows, and code push process</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1c39be681e0b"><strong>Solution Architects</strong> =E2=80=94=
 for reviewing the infrastructure design and architectural decisions</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ae11d7713a17"><strong>DevOps Engineers</strong> =E2=80=94 fo=
r replicating, maintaining, or extending this setup</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8ef56619481d"><strong>Resellers</strong> =E2=80=94 for under=
standing the solution stack and deployment model for client engagements</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"619942e6a311" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-1.2Scope">1.2 Scope</h3>
<p local-id=3D"88aa7ece5dc2">This document covers the end-to-end technical =
implementation of:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3c0d14682394">Provisioning an AWS EC2 instance and installin=
g GitLab CE</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"40645f19eeb4">Configuring GitLab CE with a custom domain (gi=
tlab.karna.pushkar.cloud)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"66a0c06db66a">Setting up admin access and creating a GitLab =
group and project repository</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7f66a48b1fe0">Pushing a Flask Hello World application from a=
 local Windows machine to the GitLab CE repository</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"00672bc03029">Upgrading the GitLab server from HTTP to HTTPS=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"59d72626b011">This document does not cover CI/CD pipeline co=
nfiguration, production Flask app deployment, GitLab EE features, or multi-=
node HA GitLab setup.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"43b54931a8a6" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-2.OverviewofDevOpsProject">2. Overview of=
 DevOps Project</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"8a03a5e6d534" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-2.1Definition">2.1 Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ac81afb6b55b">DevOps is a set of practices, tools, and cultu=
ral philosophies that automate and integrate the processes between software=
 development and IT operations teams. The goal is to shorten the systems de=
velopment lifecycle and provide continuous delivery of high-quality softwar=
e.</p>
<p local-id=3D"31547cc16263">In this project, the foundational layer of a D=
evOps toolchain =E2=80=94 a self-hosted Version Control System (VCS) using =
GitLab CE =E2=80=94 is established. This allows ABC Technologies to manage =
source code internally, enforce access controls, and build toward a full CI=
/CD pipeline in future iterations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8bf27dfb2668"><strong>Key benefits realized in this implemen=
tation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"aa38b479cc91">Full ownership of source code without reliance=
 on third-party cloud VCS platforms</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6769efc676ff">Centralized code collaboration through GitLab =
groups and projects</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0972d3e74529">Foundation for future CI/CD automation using G=
itLab Pipelines</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1106b59b3ba0">Improved security posture through self-hosted =
infrastructure with HTTPS</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"0233054b9347" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-2.2KeyPrinciples=E2=80=94AWSWell-Architec=
tedFramework(6Pillars)">2.2 Key Principles =E2=80=94 AWS Well-Architected F=
ramework (6 Pillars)</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e=
d440187-e667-4790-bf84-95ae74d79ea2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"3f8dfb051f4a">Pillar</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9fa6d076e34c">How It Was Achieved</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c1192390dd1"><strong>Operational Excellence</strong></p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4173e86b1dd1">GitLab CE was installed using official scripts=
 with a structured step-by-step process; reconfiguration was done using <co=
de>gitlab-ctl reconfigure</code> ensuring repeatable operations</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f179d7689b93"><strong>Security</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"97b6ecb61f57">SSH key-based EC2 access (PEM file), Security =
Group restrictions on ports, initial root password management, and HTTP-to-=
HTTPS upgrade implemented</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"293714893f01"><strong>Reliability</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de4664a9ec23">GitLab CE services managed by <code>gitlab-ctl=
</code>; EC2 instance selected with sufficient RAM (t2.medium/t3.medium) to=
 ensure stable operation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"893f40d0d007"><strong>Performance Efficiency</strong></p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"151961a2ae15">Right-sized EC2 instance selected based on Git=
Lab CE minimum requirements (4 GB RAM, 2 vCPUs); lightweight Flask app used=
 for validation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3459aed77d1c"><strong>Cost Optimization</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"67b8791f9875">GitLab CE (free, open-source) used instead of =
paid VCS platforms; EC2 instance sized to minimum requirements to reduce co=
st</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9f43e8162725"><strong>Sustainability</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa295194c68d">Self-hosted infrastructure reduces dependency =
on external SaaS platforms; internal knowledge built through documentation =
for long-term maintainability</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"1092b72ac0d0" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-2.3GoalsandObjectives">2.3 Goals and Obje=
ctives</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"72c1e65908e3">Deploy a stable, accessible GitLab CE server o=
n AWS EC2 with a custom domain</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c50b4cb8458f">Provide ABC Technologies with a self-hosted co=
de management platform</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7bf04ede9886">Validate the GitLab setup by successfully push=
ing a Flask Hello World application</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9cd171554226">Demonstrate standard Git workflows (init, comm=
it, remote, push) on the self-hosted platform</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9259a5174224">Upgrade the server from HTTP to HTTPS for secu=
re communication</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0205c8d361d8">Document the entire process for reproducibilit=
y and knowledge transfer</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"be0da2aeb367" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-2.4ConstraintsandAssumptions">2.4 Constra=
ints and Assumptions</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c83fdcf4db4c"><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7=
aecd436-48e6-456f-b6e3-9d98a360f2f8" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7a2231770ec5">Constraint</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cf177255cfb5">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"90fa0dae007d">Time</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f3726c29400b">Task must be completed within 3 hours</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e275ea07e8bd">Budget</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"501be7c93608">Minimal AWS cost; EC2 instance at minimum GitL=
ab-supported spec</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fbe123ced345">Technology</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3d6879072d38">GitLab CE only; no Enterprise Edition features=
 available</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c43b7a908258">OS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f97662bdd528">Ubuntu on EC2 (no Windows Server or other OS v=
ariants)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f9c9626aac7f">Network</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"62d429755207">Ports 22, 80, and 443 must be open in the EC2 =
Security Group</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"66cb4b7a4e7d">Domain</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6735773ae3d1">Custom domain must be DNS-mapped to EC2 prior =
to GitLab configuration</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"7763cccf9daa"><strong>Assumptions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0d40c9de1442">The EC2 instance is already provisioned and ru=
nning Ubuntu before implementation begins</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"51c0531f8ca2">The custom domain gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud D=
NS A record is pre-configured to the EC2 public IP</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b80177152334">Git is installed and functional on the local W=
indows machine</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7a80510f223c">A Flask Hello World repository is available fo=
r use locally</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3bff05ce58e2">The DevOps intern has AWS console access and S=
SH access to the EC2 instance</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"c7e425be2a29" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-3.ArchitectureandInfrastructure">3. Archi=
tecture and Infrastructure</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"8f37f8f9bc65" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-3.1InfrastructureOverview">3.1 Infrastruc=
ture Overview</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7e694d242a59">The solution uses a single AWS EC2 instance ru=
nning Ubuntu as the host for GitLab CE. The instance is accessible via a cu=
stom domain mapped through DNS. The local developer machine (Windows) commu=
nicates with the GitLab CE server over HTTP (later upgraded to HTTPS) for G=
it operations.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">+------=
---------------------+          +-------------------------------+
|   Local Windows Machine   |          |        AWS Cloud              |
|                           |  HTTP /  |  +-------------------------+  |
|  Git Client               |  HTTPS   |  |   EC2 Instance (Ubuntu) |  |
|  Flask Hello World Code   |---------&gt;|  |   GitLab CE Server      |  |
|                           |          |  |   gitlab-ctl services   |  |
+---------------------------+          |  +-------------------------+  |
                                       |           |                   |
                                       |    Security Group             |
                                       |    Port 22 (SSH)              |
                                       |    Port 80 (HTTP)             |
                                       |    Port 443 (HTTPS)           |
                                       |           |                   |
                                       |    Custom Domain DNS          |
                                       |  gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud   |
                                       +-------------------------------+</p=
re>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"48d3094c258f"><strong>Infrastructure Components:</strong></p=
>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5=
a765b2e-30c7-4927-b551-6d5eebac1fa1" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"644226bf2aeb">Component</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"13eeadbb9e07">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"27efb99fa9a2">Cloud Provider</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"00000e652d21">AWS</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8578c6489b1d">Compute</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"26468f07775d">EC2 Instance (Ubuntu, t2.medium or t3.medium)<=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4f300ffacd71">Storage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"22f3a3716fb0">EC2 Root EBS Volume</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6e1fe8e4b6b5">Networking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b736b0bb68f">VPC, Security Group, Public IP / Elastic IP</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a5bb6109f567">DNS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d3bcad1f49e3">Custom domain: gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"966955051b91">Application</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"018ecf073a10">GitLab CE (self-hosted)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8a002395ad37">SSH Access</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a6fc24fd4183">PEM key: t-22-k.pem</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"ef53093bf9eb" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-3.2Environments">3.2 Environments</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"1=
0039a59-62cd-4971-8fd2-b2c4fd522c8b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"dd96acbd649d">Environment</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f13c67cb2d2c">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"67479726db86"><strong>Server (EC2)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b267e1665df8">Ubuntu EC2 instance hosting the GitLab CE serv=
er; all GitLab services run here</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"592cc2d0305c"><strong>Local Development (Windows)</strong></=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"76e79062dba5">Developer's Windows machine used for writing a=
nd pushing Flask application code</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f57a5f4f354b"><strong>GitLab Repository</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c768276861f">The remote repository hosted on the EC2 GitLab=
 CE instance; acts as the central code store</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"61360e3f689e">Note: For this PoC implementation, a single en=
vironment is used. In a production setup, separate Dev, Staging, and Produc=
tion environments would be defined.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f57691d2238a" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-3.3ApplicationArchitectureandUserRequestF=
low">3.3 Application Architecture and User Request Flow</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7e15100ec560"><strong>Application Architecture:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Develop=
er (Windows)
        |
        | git push (HTTP/HTTPS)
        v
Custom Domain: gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud
        |
        | DNS A Record resolves to EC2 Public IP
        v
AWS EC2 Instance (Ubuntu)
        |
        +---&gt; GitLab NGINX (Port 80 / 443)
        |           |
        |           v
        |     GitLab Puma (App Server)
        |           |
        |           v
        |     GitLab Sidekiq (Background Jobs)
        |           |
        |           v
        |     GitLab PostgreSQL (Database)
        |           |
        |           v
        +---&gt; Git Repository Storage (EBS Volume)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"04f67c26cb8f"><strong>Secured User Request Flow (HTTP to HTT=
PS Upgrade):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Step 1:=
 Developer opens browser
        --&gt; http://gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud
        --&gt; DNS resolves to EC2 Public IP
        --&gt; NGINX on EC2 receives request on Port 80

Step 2 (After HTTPS upgrade):
        --&gt; http://gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud
        --&gt; NGINX redirects to https://gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud (Port =
443)
        --&gt; SSL/TLS handshake completed
        --&gt; GitLab UI served securely

Step 3: Git Push from Windows
        --&gt; git push origin main
        --&gt; Credentials validated by GitLab (root / PAT)
        --&gt; Code stored in GitLab repository on EBS</pre>
</div>
</div>
