<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"b538e40aa4e8" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-12.Conclusion">12. Conclusion</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"bab70be7ffee" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-12.1Summary">12.1 Summary</h3>
<p local-id=3D"0b4c4b486910">This document has detailed the end-to-end tech=
nical implementation of a self-hosted GitLab CE server on AWS EC2 for ABC T=
echnologies. The key achievements of this implementation are:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"810ddd348356">A fully functional GitLab CE server deployed o=
n EC2 and accessible at a custom domain (gitlab.karna.pushkar.cloud)</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"89c7b8b9acd8">GitLab CE configured with admin access, a grou=
p (karna-grp), and a project repository (task-22-karna)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"778dbb08b4b1">A Flask Hello World application successfully p=
ushed from a local Windows machine to the self-hosted GitLab repository usi=
ng standard Git workflows</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"07fbe94c28ae">The server upgraded from HTTP to HTTPS for sec=
ure access</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"24c990e74e1a">The AWS Well-Architected Framework principles =
applied across all 6 pillars</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c7a850177623">TCO analysis demonstrating cost-effectiveness =
compared to SaaS alternatives</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"eca5c02bbf98">This implementation establishes the foundation=
al infrastructure for ABC Technologies' internal DevOps toolchain and creat=
es a reproducible, documented process for future team members.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"cf9e7e836f75" id=3D"Task22-SettingUpaGitLabCEServerandPushi=
ngaFlaskHelloWorldApplicationcode-12.2NextSteps">12.2 Next Steps</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"68c31f5a08c1"><strong>Immediate:</strong> Add SSH keys to th=
e GitLab user profile and use SSH-based Git operations to eliminate passwor=
d prompts</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a34e1a5cc41b"><strong>Short-term:</strong> Configure GitLab =
CI/CD with a <code>.gitlab-ci.yml</code> file and register a GitLab Runner =
for automated testing and deployment</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f63a5b18688a"><strong>Short-term:</strong> Set up automated =
GitLab backups to AWS S3 to prevent data loss</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c242cb036420"><strong>Medium-term:</strong> Create individua=
l user accounts; enforce Merge Request workflows with code review before me=
rging to main</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"510baba17dfd"><strong>Medium-term:</strong> Integrate Promet=
heus and Grafana for monitoring GitLab service health</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"610d1f841bf1"><strong>Long-term:</strong> Evaluate GitLab EE=
 features (LDAP integration, advanced CI/CD, security scanning) as the team=
 grows</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
